# Student Course Manager API

Simple educational project (C# / .NET 8 Web API) for practicing backend development, database connections, and API testing. Provides CRUD operations for students, courses and enrollments, plus XML export and basic logging/tests.

## Tech stack
- Language: C# (.NET 8)
- Framework: ASP.NET Core Web API
- Database: SQL Server or SQLite (via EF Core)
- Data formats: JSON, XML
- Testing: xUnit
- Docs: Swagger
- Logging: Serilog
- VCS: Git / GitHub
- IDE: Visual Studio / Rider

## Main features
- CRUD for Students, Courses, Enrollments
- Swagger UI for interactive API docs
- Export reports in XML format
- EF Core database integration
- Serilog file logging
- Unit tests (xUnit)
- Basic validation and error handling

## Project structure
StudentCourseManager
- StudentCourseManager.API — Controllers, Swagger, Program/Startup
- StudentCourseManager.Core — Entities, DTOs, interfaces, services
- StudentCourseManager.Data — DbContext and repositories
- StudentCourseManager.Tests — Unit tests (xUnit)
- README — Project documentation

## Quick start (local)
1. Clone repository:
   git clone https://github.com/Asdeks/StudentCourseManager.git
2. Open solution or change directory:
   cd StudentCourseManager
3. Run API:
   dotnet run --project StudentCourseManager.API
4. Open Swagger UI:
   http://localhost:5000/swagger

(Port may vary depending on launch settings — check console output.)

## Example endpoints
- GET /api/students — list students
- POST /api/students — create student
- GET /api/courses — list courses
- POST /api/enrollments — enroll student in course
- GET /api/reports/export — export report in XML

## Tests
Run unit tests:
dotnet test

## Notes & learning goals
This is a small pet project created to:
- Refresh C# / .NET Web API skills
- Practice EF Core and SQL
- Work with JSON/XML serialization
- Learn test writing and logging
Planned future improvements: other DB integrations, messaging, improved validation.

